Now looking in the Safari console, a javascript error occurs when trying to display the accuracy graphs :

More info : 
- problem occurs in Firefox 49.0.2 (Mac OS X El Capitan), Firefox 47.0.1 (Windows 7)
- problem occurs in Safari Version 10.0 (11602.1.50.0.10) (Mac OS X El Capitan)
- Events graphs are well displayed with Google Chrome 54.0.2840.71 (Window 7) 

Now looking in the Safari console, a javascript error occurs when trying to display the accuracy graphs : 
[Warning] Warning: Problem parsing viewBox="" (d3.js, line 662)

```
    function attrConstant() {
      this.setAttribute(name, value);          # <---- Problem parsing viewBox=""
    }
```

In fact the same error occurs in Google Chrome but it seems more fault tolerant as the graph is well displayed in the end
